For nncscale image build: `make build-push`

For skale image build: 
`cd ./../skale`
`go build -o ../nodereadiness/skale`

Testing commands:
`./test-vnetscale.sh <nodes:int> <delandrecreate:bool>`
where `nodes` is the number of nodes you want to create
and `delandrecreate` is whether to delete and recreate 50%
of the nodes. (E.g. `./test-vnetscale.sh 50 true`).
This command may be combined with `task prom` to view metrics
and `task teardown` to clean up after the test.

Testing commands:
`task kwok` in a separate terminal.

`task setup` -> Set up pods on cluster.
`task prom` -> Prometheus at localhost:9002
`task graf` -> Set up local Grafana (assuming it is installed) at localhost:3000
`task skale-1000` -> Scale up to 1000 Kwok nodes.

Cleanup:
`task scaledown` -> Scale down Kwok nodes.
`task teardown` -> Teardown cluster state.



# For Podman login
sudo apt-get install podman -y

# GET ACR creds
az acr credential show --name acnpublic 

returns:
{
  "passwords": [
    {
      "name": "password",
      "value": "pass1"
    },
    {
      "name": "password2",
      "value": "pass2"
    }
  ],
  "username": "acnpublic"
}

# Login to ACR through podman
podman login acnpublic.azurecr.io -u acnpublic -p <pass>